execute

public boolean execute(CommandInterpreter interpreter,
                       java.lang.String argsString,
                       boolean batchMode)
Execute this command with the given args, returning the status of the execution (true=ok, false=error).

Note that any error or response to be printed by the interpreter needs to be handled here.

Specified by:
execute in interface CommandExecutor
Parameters:
interpreter - the interpreter executing the command.
argsString - string containing arguments for the command.
batchMode - true if interpreter is operating in batchMode; false if interactive.
Returns:
true for successful execution (from the interpreter's standpoint); otherwise, false.
